## Description {#details}

This file defines the SparseMultiSet class, which adds multiset behavior to the SparseSet.

A sparse multiset holds a small number of objects identified by integer keys from a moderately sized universe. The sparse multiset uses more memory than other containers in order to provide faster operations. Any key can map to multiple values. A SparseMultiSetNode class is provided, which serves as a convenient base class for the contents of a SparseMultiSet.

<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Fast multiset implementation for objects that can be identified by small</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">/// unsigned keys.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SparseMultiSet allocates memory proportional to the size of the key</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// universe, so it is not recommended for building composite data structures.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It is useful for algorithms that require a single set with fast operations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Compared to DenseSet and DenseMap, SparseMultiSet provides constant-time</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">/// fast clear() as fast as a vector.  The find(), insert(), and erase()</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment">/// operations are all constant time, and typically faster than a hash table.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The iteration order doesn&#39;t depend on numerical key values, it only depends</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">/// on the order of insert() and erase() operations.  Iteration order is the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">/// insertion order. Iteration is only provided over elements of equivalent</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">/// keys, but iterators are bidirectional.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Compared to BitVector, SparseMultiSet&lt;unsigned&gt; uses 8x-40x more memory, but</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><Highlight kind="comment">/// offers constant-time clear() and size() operations as well as fast iteration</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><Highlight kind="comment">/// independent on the size of the universe.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SparseMultiSet contains a dense vector holding all the objects and a sparse</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><Highlight kind="comment">/// array holding indexes into the dense vector.  Most of the memory is used by</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the sparse array which is the size of the key universe. The SparseT template</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><Highlight kind="comment">/// parameter provides a space/speed tradeoff for sets holding many elements.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When SparseT is uint32&#95;t, find() only touches up to 3 cache lines, but the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><Highlight kind="comment">/// sparse array uses 4 x Universe bytes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When SparseT is uint8&#95;t (the default), find() touches up to 3+&#91;N/256&#93; cache</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><Highlight kind="comment">/// lines, but the sparse array is 4x smaller.  N is the number of elements in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the set.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For sets that may grow to thousands of elements, SparseT should be set to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><Highlight kind="comment">/// uint16&#95;t or uint32&#95;t.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Multiset behavior is provided by providing doubly linked lists for values</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that are inlined in the dense vector. SparseMultiSet is a good choice when</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><Highlight kind="comment">/// one desires a growable number of entries per key, as it will retain the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SparseSet algorithmic properties despite being growable. Thus, it is often a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><Highlight kind="comment">/// better choice than a SparseSet of growable containers or a vector of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><Highlight kind="comment">/// vectors. SparseMultiSet also keeps iterators valid after erasure (provided</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the iterators don&#39;t point to the element erased), allowing for more</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><Highlight kind="comment">/// intuitive and fast removal.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a5bb43880c7874561f71afdebbc59e2ed"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a3a0e116fdaa2041ec3d61c9d110b0c2f">size&#95;type</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a5bb43880c7874561f71afdebbc59e2ed">size</a>()</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword"> const </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">&#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(NumFree &lt;= Dense.size() &amp;&amp; </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;Out-of-bounds free entries&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a2554bf4e6f211e29c3e80fd4c9141c79"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a2554bf4e6f211e29c3e80fd4c9141c79">clear</a>() &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Stride is 0 when SparseT &gt;= unsigned.  We don&#39;t need to loop.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="441"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Erases an existing element identified by a valid iterator.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This invalidates iterators pointing at the same entry, but erase() returns</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// an iterator pointing to the next element in the subset&#39;s list. This makes</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="446"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// it possible to erase selected elements while iterating over the subset:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="447"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00448" /><CodeLine lineNumber="448"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   tie(I, E) = Set.equal&#95;range(Key);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="449"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   while (I != E)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00450" /><CodeLine lineNumber="450"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     if (test(&#42;I))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00451" /><CodeLine lineNumber="451"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///       I = Set.erase(I);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00452" /><CodeLine lineNumber="452"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     else</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00453" /><CodeLine lineNumber="453"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///       ++I;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00454" /><CodeLine lineNumber="454"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00455" /><CodeLine lineNumber="455"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Note that if the last element in the subset list is erased, this will</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00456" /><CodeLine lineNumber="456"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// return an end iterator which can be decremented to get the new tail (if it</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00457" /><CodeLine lineNumber="457"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// exists):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00458" /><CodeLine lineNumber="458"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00459" /><CodeLine lineNumber="459"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  tie(B, I) = Set.equal&#95;range(Key);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00460" /><CodeLine lineNumber="460"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  for (bool isBegin = B == I; !isBegin; /&#42; empty &#42;/) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00461" /><CodeLine lineNumber="461"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    isBegin = (--I) == B;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00462" /><CodeLine lineNumber="462"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    if (test(I))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00463" /><CodeLine lineNumber="463"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///      break;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    I = erase(I);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  &#125;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a3ab390f0c1123852f16664da01de672a"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#ada97379dfb89c01fb4065e33bf180f0e">iterator</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#a3ab390f0c1123852f16664da01de672a">erase</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparsemultiset/#ada97379dfb89c01fb4065e33bf180f0e">iterator</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00467" /><CodeLine lineNumber="467"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>.isKeyed() &amp;&amp; !<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>.isEnd() &amp;&amp; !Dense&#91;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>.Idx&#93;.isTombstone() &amp;&amp;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00468" /><CodeLine lineNumber="468"><Highlight kind="normal">           </Highlight><Highlight kind="stringliteral">&quot;erasing invalid/end/tombstone iterator&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00469" /><CodeLine lineNumber="469"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
